.TH "BREW\-MAN" "1" "April 2026" "Homebrew"
.SH NAME
brew\-man \- Display a man page bundled with an installed formula
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBbrew\fP \fBman\fP [\fIoptions\fP] \fIformula\fP [\fImanpage\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Display a man page bundled with an installed formula\.
.P
In normal mode, shows the man page for \fImanpage\fP (defaulting to the formula name) from \fIformula\fP\[u2019]s keg using the system \fBman\fP viewer\. With \fB\-\-html\fP, renders the man page via \fBmandoc \-T html\fP and opens it in a browser\.
.P
In \fB\-\-list\fP mode, shows all locations where a given man page is found (both system paths and Homebrew formula kegs)\.
.P
In \fB\-\-select\fP mode, presents a numbered list to interactively choose which copy of a man page to view\.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
\fB\-d\fP, \fB\-\-debug\fP
Display any debugging information\.
.TP
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
Make some output more quiet\.
.TP
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-verbose\fP
Make some output more verbose\.
.TP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
Show this message\.
.TP
\fB\-H\fP, \fB\-\-html\fP
Render the man page as HTML and open it in a browser\.
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fP
List all locations where the named man page is found\.
.TP
\fB\-\-select\fP
Interactively select which copy of the man page to view\.
